  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "display_name": "Sam",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. **Look** at your user profile to understand their needs and challenges.\r\n\r\n2. **Drag** each checklist box onto the part of the app where it applies.\r\n\r\n3. **Mark** the box to show how well the design works for your user:\r\n\r\n    * If it works well, color it green or add a check.\r\n    \r\n    * If it doesn't work well, color it red or add an X.\r\n\r\n4. **Point** an arrow to the part of the app that works well or needs improvement.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**User Profile:**\r\n\r\n\r\n- **Name**: Sam\r\n- **Age**: 32\r\n- Uses a tablet or laptop to manage school lunch orders for two kids.\r\n- Balances work and parenting and needs to complete tasks quickly.\r\n- Struggles with tiny text, too many steps, or unclear confirmations.\r\n\r\n",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Sam uses a tablet or laptop to order school lunches. Help check if the app is organized, clear, and easy to complete tasks quickly.",
